The average kill is worth {{Coins|floor({{#var:onekill}})}}, however if not counting in any uniques the kill would only be worth {{Coins|floor({{#var:stdroll}}*{{#var:stdtableroll}}+{{GEP|Hydra bones|2}})}}. Due to this, the profit from Hydra is highly dependent on its uniques: [[Hydra leather]], [[Hydra's claw]], and the three hydra parts required to make the [[Brimstone ring]] - the [[Hydra's eye]], [[Hydra's fang|fang]] and [[Hydra's heart|heart]].

[[High Level Alchemy|High alchemy]] runes should be brought to extend trips. Extended trips often result in the inability to pick up the hydra bones dropped from every kill. Despite this, extended trips typically lead to higher kills per hour, increasing profit over time.

See the [[Alchemical Hydra]] article and the [[Alchemical Hydra/Strategies|strategy guide]] for additional information.
